<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mantle1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mantle,</orth> subst. 1) cloak: <bibl n="shak. luc 170" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 79" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 143</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 143</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 174</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.5.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 5, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.361" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 361</bibl>. Used of the darkness of night: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 2, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 2, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 15</bibl>. of the twilight of morning: <cit><quote>the morn, in russet m. clad,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 166</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) that which gathers on the surface of a pool: <cit><quote>the green m. of the standing pool,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 139</bibl></cit>.
